{
  "texts": [
    "This is accomplished primarily by poisoning a portion of training data with triggers, which causes the model to learn incorrect correlations.",
    "Previous research [78,169] has illustrated the severe outcomes of backdoor attacks on LLMs.",
    "Given that agents based on LLMs employ these models as their core component, it is plausible to assert that such agents are also significantly vulnerable to these attacks.In contrast to conventional LLMs that directly produce final outputs, agents accomplish tasks through executing multi-step intermediate processes and optionally interacting with the environment to gather external context prior to output generation.",
    "This expanded input space of AI agents offers attackers more diverse attack vectors, such as the ability to manipulate any stage of the agents' intermediate reasoning processes.",
    "Yang et al. [192] categorized two types of backdoor attacks against agents.First, the distribution of the final output is altered."
  ]
}